<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA VOICES / A FORUM FOR COMMUNITY ISSUES: GALLERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What do young people see as their landmarks? The Getty Conservation Institute 
in West Los Angeles asked that question in 1992.It got answers by loaning 
cameras to a group of ethnically diverse teen-agers who recorded places they 
found important. Their fresh, affecting images, including those at right, will 
be displayed starting Wednesday at the Henry P. Rio Bridge Gallery in Los 
Angeles City Hall. The show ends Jan. 6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
