<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA VOICES / A FORUM FOR COMMUNITY ISSUES: HORSES IN ARROYO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Having gone to considerable lengths to stress serious concerns regarding 
trail-safety issues, I was most disappointed to see our most pertinent argument 
was edited from my statement in the Nov. 14 In the Neighborhood ("Arroyo Seco: 
Whose Needs Come First?") 
</P>
<P>
 Although we are by no means the only folks to object to changing the standing 
ordinance (restricting bikes on trails), we are the group that would be most 
severely impacted by the very real danger of serious accidents that can -- and 
have -- occurred with the advent of bicycles onto hiking/bridle trails. 
</P>
<P>
 SANDRA SMITH SPECHT 
</P>
<P>
 Equestrian Trails International 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena 
</P>
</TEXT>
