<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA VOICES / A FORUM FOR COMMUNITY ISSUES: IT'S JUST GOOD 
MANNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 We love the Voices page with views of people from every walk of life. But the 
Nov. 14 Multicultural Manners, "Shoeless Salesman Lands on His Feet," about not 
jumping to conclusions about everyone whose ancestors came from a certain 
continental area like Asia, really struck me. What everyone should rely on is 
their own sense of fairness, consideration of others' feelings and compassion 
for the situation of others -- in short, plain good manners, not 
"multicultural" manners. 
</P>
<P>
 JOANNE H. GRAM 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor; Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
