<HEADLINE>
<P>
VOLLEYBALL; LONG BEACH GIVES MONTANA TASTE OF CHAMPIONSHIP PLAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON REID, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Determined and confident, Montana quickly encountered the reality of women's 
volleyball, West Coast style. 
</P>
<P>
 Defending national champion Long Beach State overwhelmed the Grizzlies, 15-10, 
15-6, 15-8, Sunday in the second round of the NCAA Tournament's Northwest 
Regionals before 1,757 at the Pyramid. 
</P>
<P>
 "This was a little bit of a different level of play for them," Long Beach 
Coach Brian Gimmillaro said. "We play a little faster and a little higher than 
they do." 
</P>
<P>
 Junior outside hitter Brita Schwerm led the 49ers (26-5) with a match-high 17 
kills. Senior middle blocker Traci Dahl had 12 kills and seven total blocks. 
Nichelle Burton -- the 49ers' senior All-American outside hitter and Big West 
Conference player of the year -- also played well despite being slowed by a 
sprained right ankle. She contributed 11 kills and a match-high 13 digs. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach, ranked seventh in the nation and seeded second in the region, will 
be host for the regional semifinals and final this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge defeated San Jose State, 15-4, 15-13, 13-15, 15-6, at 
Kansas City to win the National Invitational Tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Bakersfield defeated Northern Colorado, 7-15, 18-16, 15-5, 15-13, in 
the semifinals of the NCAA Division II tournament at Bakersfield and will play 
Northern Michigan for the title tonight. 
</P>
