<HEADLINE>
<P>
SMITH DUNKS BELIEF THAT WOMEN CAN'T 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Charlotte Smith of North Carolina became the first woman in 10 years to dunk a 
basketball during a game Sunday, making a one-handed jam during a rout of North 
Carolina A&T. 
</P>
<P>
 The six-foot senior intercepted a pass by Samara Dobbins and went in 
uncontested.Her right wrist cleared the rim and Smith pushed the ball through 
the basket only 17 seconds into the game. 
</P>
<P>
 "The pass was just there, and the whole time I was going out, I was focusing 
on dunking and just getting it over with," Smith said after scoring 22 points 
for the fifth-ranked Tar Heels in a 113-58 victory. "I don't know exactly what 
happened as far as gripping it. It wasn't the most convincing dunk that I've 
done, but, hey." 
</P>
<P>
 The last woman to dunk during a game was Georgeann Wells, who had two dunks 
while playing for West Virginia in 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
