<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA; DREXLER'S SHOT AT BUZZER GIVES BLAZERS A VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Clyde Drexler made a 25-foot turnaround jumper with 0.9 seconds left as the 
Portland Trail Blazers handed the Milwaukee Bucks their seventh consecutive 
loss, 106-103, Sunday night in Portland. 
</P>
<P>
 Drexler, who scored 28 of his 36 points in the second half, also had 11 
rebounds and nine assists. Harvey Grant came off the bench to score 24 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Glenn Robinson led Milwaukee with 25 points and Eric Murdock had 20, including 
16 in a fourth-quarter rally that allowed Milwaukee to tie the score at 103 in 
the final seconds. 
</P>
<P>
 After a timeout, James Robinson inbounded to Drexler on the left side. The 
guard spun and banked the shot in as the buzzer sounded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
