<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Think of an old-fashioned theater organ and you think of the once-grand 
downtown movie palaces of a half a century ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton's modest Plummer Auditorium probably doesn't come to mind.But this 
auditorium -- owned by the Fullerton Joint Union High School District -- is 
home to a mighty Wurlitzer organ. 
</P>
<P>
 Built in the 1930s, the instrument is probably the largest theater organ on 
public display in Southern California, said Bob Trousdale, owner of the 
Trousdale Organ Company. 
</P>
<P>
 The 70-year-old Santa Ana resident renovated the organ's electronic system in 
1993, and is now leading a volunteer effort to further enhance this "king of 
instruments," as theater organs are affectionately called. 
</P>
<P>
 Today 
</P>
<P>
 Westminster will usher in the holiday season tonight with a special program in 
front of City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 The public is invited to attend a concert and holiday sing-along.  
</P>
<P>
 The highlight of the program will be the lighting of a Christmas tree. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will take place at 6:30 p.m. in front of the City Council chambers, 
8200 Westminster Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is free. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, please call the city at (714) 895-2860. 
</P>
