<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; VANDALIZED HOUSE GETS REPAIR HELP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police officers and Explorer Scouts on Tuesday will clean and repair an 
elderly woman's house, which was vandalized by a local gang that includes her 
daughter, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police did not identify the woman, but said her 35-year-old daughter invited 
members of the 17th Street Gang to live in the house while her mother was 
vacationing in Northern California. 
</P>
<P>
 Police Capt. Dave Abrecht said the gang members destroyed the inside of the 
house and rendered it uninhabitable. The daughter, who has a criminal history, 
was arrested for outstanding warrants and is being held at County Jail, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Abrecht said that the clean-up effort will demonstrate that "we will not 
tolerate the senseless, destructive and violent behavior . . . of gang members 
who have no regard for people and their property." 
</P>
<P>
 Code enforcement officials and volunteers also will help clean the home on 
Havenwood Street. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
