<P>
BUENA PARK MAN IS FATALLY SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 23-year-old Buena Park man died early Sunday several hours after he was shot 
in a residential area, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police drove to the 500 block of South Resh Street after receiving reports 
that several shots had been fired at 2:10 a.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Officers found a bleeding man lying on the road, police said. He had been shot 
several times in the upper body and was rushed to the UCI Medical Center in 
Orange.  
</P>
<P>
 The man died several hours later, Sgt. Steve Rodig said. Police would not 
disclose the identity of the victim. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have no suspects, and the motive for the shooting is unknown. 
</P>
