<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; GOLDEN WEST WINS SECOND STATE TITLE IN ROW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Becca Foltz earned her second consecutive most valuable player award as Golden 
West won its second consecutive State women's volleyball title with a victory 
over Cerritos on Sunday at DeAnza College in Cupertino. 
</P>
<P>
 Foltz, a sophomore outside hitter from Foothill High, had 17 kills in the 
title match as the Rustlers swept, 15-12, 17-15, 15-9. 
</P>
<P>
 Vanessa Dahl added 15 kills for Golden West, which has won four of the last 
five State titles under Coach Albert Gasparian. 
</P>
<P>
 Dahl and Christine Heims, along with Foltz, were selected to the 
all-tournament team for Golden West (25-2). 
</P>
<P>
 The Rustlers' two losses this season came to Cerritos in a tournament in 
October. 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos (22-2) lost twice to Golden West, both times in the State tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 "We put it together as a team for a weekend," Gasparian said. "You could tell 
Tuesday against Mt. San Antonio (in a playoff game) that we were starting to 
click." 
</P>
<P>
 In the College of the Sequoias women's basketball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West 75, Fullerton 52 -- Deana Itow and Julie Murdent each scored 19 
points and April Van Sweden added nine to lead Golden West (9-3) to the 
consolation title. Lupe Janos and Vanessa Trujillo each scored 13 points for 
Fullerton (6-4). 
</P>
</TEXT>
