<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: GROUP WILL MEET TO REVIEW NAVY CLEANUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KENNETH R. WEISS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Restoration Advisory Board, a group of military and community 
representatives reviewing the toxic cleanup of U. S. Navy property, will hold 
its next meeting Wednesday night in Port Hueneme. 
</P>
<P>
 The Navy is in various stages of cleaning up old spills of toxic materials at 
the Naval Construction Battalion Center in Port Hueneme, the Naval Air Weapons 
Stations at Point Mugu and the former Naval Civil Engineering Laboratory at the 
mouth of the Port of Hueneme. 
</P>
<P>
 The board meeting will be held from 7 to 9 p.m. at the Orvene Carpenter 
Community Center, 550 Park Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The board is still accepting members. For information, call Gail Pringle at 
982-2105. KENNETH R. WEISS 
</P>
