WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; MAN, 83, DIES AFTER BEING STRUCK BY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 83-year-old Oxnard man was killed after being struck by a car while walking 
in the street near his home, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Dominador Elayda Eclarino died at St. John's Regional Medical Center as a 
result of head injuries he suffered when a car driven by Elsie Nordstrom hit 
him. The incident occurred on Patricia Street near Bevra Avenue in Oxnard about 
9:20 p.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Eclarino couldn't sleep and was out walking when he was struck, Senior Deputy 
Coroner Dale Zentzis said. He died a short time later at the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Nordstrom was questioned by police and released, pending further 
investigation. JEFF McDONALD 
