WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; POLICE GANG SWEEP NETS 30 SUSPECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Oxnard Police Department gang sweep resulted in more than 30 arrests, 
including for four felonies and the recovery of a stolen firearm, officials 
said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The department's gang-enforcement team contacted more than 115 suspected gang 
members over three nights ending Saturday, Sgt. Charles Hookstra said. 
</P>
<P>
 The officers made four felony arrests, two misdemeanor arrests and 25 arrests 
for alleged violations of the city's curfew law. Of the four felony arrests, 
three of those taken into custody were Oxnard juveniles arrested on suspicion 
of stealing a car, burglary and possession of a .357-Magnum revolver, Hookstra 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The increased enforcement was planned in response to an escalating series of 
gang incidents over the past several weeks, including three drive-by shootings, 
he said. JEFF McDONALD 
