<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIZ SMITH: IT'S BACK TO BASICS FOR 007 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LIZ SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Here's good news about the script of "Goldeneye," Pierce Brosnan's coming 
debut as James Bond. It will not be politically correct! 
</P>
<P>
 This means -- among other things -- plenty of surgically enhanced lovelies who 
want to kill 007 or bed him. Or both. (I see "The Girls of Goldeneye" in a 
future edition of Playboy!) 
</P>
<P>
 The film's two bad guys are Sean Bean (you might remember his well-muscled 
anatomy from "Lady Chatterley's Lover") and Robbie Coltrane (A&E's "Cracker"). 
Robbie plays the head of the Russian Mafia. 
</P>
<P>
 Filming on "Goldeneye" begins in January. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Sophia Loren agreed to do only one magazine interview promoting her appearance 
in Robert Altman's "Ready to Wear" ("Pret-a-Porter"). And that magazine is the 
delicious Detour. 
</P>
<P>
 You can't miss Sophia on the cover, photographed by Greg Gorman. Her 
cheekbones, lips and incredible cleavage are apparently indestructible! 
</P>
<P>
 Altman certainly thought so. He persuaded Sophia to re-create her famous 
striptease from "Yesterday, Today and Tomorrow" for his movie. 
</P>
<P>
 When writer Jim Turner asks Sophia how it feels to be 60, Loren replies 
cheerfully, "I am not 60. I am three times 20!" The enduring star adds that 
"inside, I am still 12 years old." 
</P>
</TEXT>
