<TEXT>
<P>
 Foreign Investment Rises 44%: In the first 10 months of the year, foreign 
investment in China rose 44% to $25.234 billion, the official China media 
reports.What investors have pledged to spend in the future continued to drop, 
however, with $62.58 billion promised for 37,735 projects through October. This 
year is certain to top last year's $26 billion, according to the newspapers. 
Last year only the United States attracted more foreign investment, with $32 
billion. Overseas companies are keen to tap into the world's fastest-growing 
economy and most-populous market. Since China began opening to the world in 
1978, foreigners have invested $83 billion. 
