<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUPLE DIE IN APPARENT MURDER-SUICIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 61-year-old man man who may have been distraught over marital problems shot 
and killed his wife Sunday in their El Monte home and then killed himself, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's Deputy Brian Jones said the couple's grown son found the two dead on 
the same bed, and a small semiautomatic gun was found on the floor nearby. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple's names were not released Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
 "Investigators have learned that the couple has had past marital problems," 
Jones said. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbor Juan Lara said the man had said the two were divorcing. 
</P>
