<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEARCH CONTINUES FOR 3 MISSING ON PLANE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Search teams canvassed the Kern County area Sunday in hopes of learning what 
had happened to three Long Beach men aboard a single-engine plane missing for a 
week after an apparent crash, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 But the day's efforts provided few new leads, and bad weather in the region 
grounded air crews for a second consecutive day, said Lt. Col. Sydney J. Wolfe 
of the Civil Air Patrol. Because of stormy weather, officials do not expect to 
resume air searches for the trio until Tuesday, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Missing are pilot Peter J. Deleo, 33, and two passengers, Waverly Hatch, 49, 
and Lloyd Matsumoto, 55. Wolfe said the three men left Long Beach Airport on 
Nov. 27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
