<HEADLINE>
<P>
4,000 MARCH IN CHAMBER'S HOLIDAY PARADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hundreds of San Fernando Valley residents -- toting chairs, blankets and 
containers of hot cocoa -- lined Chatsworth Street in Granada Hills on Sunday 
for the 11th annual Holiday Parade.This year's festivities included 4,000 
participants from more than 150 groups, making it the Granada Hills Chamber of 
Commerce's largest parade to date. 
</P>
<P>
 Mark and Caren Pinson were among the first to stake out a prime curbside spot. 
Although they've been coming to the parade for years to watch some of their 
eight children march through the streets, this was the first year that the 
entire brood made it onto one float. "One way or another, they've all been 
involved," Mark Pinson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
